sentences: Austin Peralta was born on October 25, 1990 to filmmaker Joni Caldwell and Z-Boys skateboarder and film director Stacy Peralta.
In 2003 at age 12, Peralta was awarded the Shelly Manne New Talent Award by the Los Angeles Jazz Society, which was presented to him by Quincy Jones.
At age 15, he performed at the 2006 Tokyo Jazz Festival with his group, The Hour Trio, and with Chick Corea and Hank Jones.
In 2006, he released two albums: Maiden Voyage with bassist Ron Carter and Mantra with bassist Buster Williams.
In 2007, he performed at the Java Jazz Festival.
In 2011, Peralta met Steven Ellison (a.k.a.
and appeared on the track "DMT Song" on the album Until the Quiet Comes (2012).
Peralta died on November 21, 2012, at the age of 22.
They performed live together at the Roy O. Disney Theatre on July 7, 2010 and numerous other occasions.

sentences: Austin Topper Peralta (October 25, 1990 – November 21, 2012) was an American jazz pianist and composer from Los Angeles, California.
Peralta studied classical piano for five years at Pepperdine University and later with jazz pianist Alan Pasqua and saxophonist Buddy Collette.
At age 15, he performed at the 2006 Tokyo Jazz Festival with his group, The Hour Trio, and with Chick Corea and Hank Jones.
